Install Docker
==============
yum install docker
       or 
1. Remove old versions of docker (if any)
dnf remove docker docker-client docker-client-latest docker-common docker-latest docker-latest-logrotate docker-logrotate docker-engine
2. Set up the Docker repository
dnf -y install dnf-plugins-core
dnf config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo
3. Install Docker Engine
dnf install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-compose-plugin -y
4. Enable and start Docker
systemctl enable --now docker

Install Kubectl
===============
Refer web page "https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-linux/"

                 or run below commands directly
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"

sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

kubectl version --client

Install Kind
============
Refer "https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/docs/user/quick-start/"

# For AMD64 / x86_64
[ $(uname -m) = x86_64 ] && curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.31.0/kind-linux-amd64
# For ARM64
[ $(uname -m) = aarch64 ] && curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.31.0/kind-linux-arm64
chmod +x ./kind
sudo mv ./kind /usr/local/bin/kind

Create cluster with single node
kind create cluster --name my-2

check cluster list
kind get clusters

check docker running container
docker ps

To create multi node cluster

kind: Cluster
apiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4
nodes:
- role: control-plane
- role: worker
- role: worker

To check currently you are interacting with which cluster(when you have multi node cluster)
kubectl config current-context

if you want to jump from one cluster to another
kubectl config get-contexts
kubectl config use-context <cluster-name>

get cluster info
kubectl cluster-info --context kind-my-2
or
kubectl cluster-info

To delete cluster
kind delete cluster --name <clustername>
